This article is about the Danish territory. For the island itself, see [Geography of Greenland](/wiki/Geography_of_Greenland "Geography of Greenland"). For other uses, see [Greenland (disambiguation)](/wiki/Greenland_(disambiguation) "Greenland (disambiguation)").

**Greenland**[[d]](#cite_note-15) is an [autonomous territory](/wiki/Autonomous_territory "Autonomous territory")[[e]](#cite_note-18) in the [Kingdom of Denmark](/wiki/Danish_Realm "Danish Realm").[[14]](#cite_note-19)[[15]](#cite_note-20) It is by far the largest geographically of three constituent parts of the kingdom; the other two are metropolitan [Denmark](/wiki/Denmark "Denmark") and the [Faroe Islands](/wiki/Faroe_Islands "Faroe Islands"). It shares a small 1.2 km border with [Canada](/wiki/Canada "Canada") on [Hans Island](/wiki/Hans_Island "Hans Island"). Citizens of Greenland are full [citizens of Denmark](/wiki/Danish_nationality_law "Danish nationality law") and [of the European Union](/wiki/European_Union_citizenship "European Union citizenship"). Greenland is one of the [Overseas Countries and Territories](/wiki/Special_territories_of_members_of_the_European_Economic_Area#Overseas_countries_and_territories "Special territories of members of the European Economic Area") of the [European Union](/wiki/European_Union "European Union") and is part of the [Council of Europe](/wiki/Council_of_Europe "Council of Europe").[[16]](#cite_note-worldfactbook-21) It is the [world's largest island](/wiki/List_of_islands_by_area "List of islands by area"),[[f]](#cite_note-23) and lies between the [Arctic](/wiki/Arctic_Ocean "Arctic Ocean") and Atlantic oceans, east of the [Canadian Arctic Archipelago](/wiki/Arctic_Archipelago "Arctic Archipelago"). Greenland's [Kaffeklubben Island](/wiki/Kaffeklubben_Island "Kaffeklubben Island"), off the northern coast, is the world's [northernmost undisputed point of land](/wiki/Northernmost_point_of_land "Northernmost point of land")[[g]](#cite_note-24)‚Äî[Cape Morris Jesup](/wiki/Cape_Morris_Jesup "Cape Morris Jesup") on the mainland was thought to be so until the 1960s. The capital and largest city is [Nuuk](/wiki/Nuuk "Nuuk").[[16]](#cite_note-worldfactbook-21) Economically, Greenland is heavily reliant on [aid from Denmark](/wiki/Block_grant#Denmark "Block grant"), amounting to nearly half of the territory's total public revenue.

This article is about the Danish territory. For the island itself, see [Geography of Greenland](/wiki/Geography_of_Greenland "Geography of Greenland"). For other uses, see [Greenland (disambiguation)](/wiki/Greenland_(disambiguation) "Greenland (disambiguation)").

**Greenland**[[d]](#cite_note-15) is an [autonomous territory](/wiki/Autonomous_territory "Autonomous territory")[[e]](#cite_note-18) in the [Kingdom of Denmark](/wiki/Danish_Realm "Danish Realm").[[14]](#cite_note-19)[[15]](#cite_note-20) It is by far the largest geographically of three constituent parts of the kingdom; the other two are metropolitan [Denmark](/wiki/Denmark "Denmark") and the [Faroe Islands](/wiki/Faroe_Islands "Faroe Islands"). It shares a small 1.2 km border with [Canada](/wiki/Canada "Canada") on [Hans Island](/wiki/Hans_Island "Hans Island"). Citizens of Greenland are full [citizens of Denmark](/wiki/Danish_nationality_law "Danish nationality law") and [of the European Union](/wiki/European_Union_citizenship "European Union citizenship"). Greenland is one of the [Overseas Countries and Territories](/wiki/Special_territories_of_members_of_the_European_Economic_Area#Overseas_countries_and_territories "Special territories of members of the European Economic Area") of the [European Union](/wiki/European_Union "European Union") and is part of the [Council of Europe](/wiki/Council_of_Europe "Council of Europe").[[16]](#cite_note-worldfactbook-21) It is the [world's largest island](/wiki/List_of_islands_by_area "List of islands by area"),[[f]](#cite_note-23) and lies between the [Arctic](/wiki/Arctic_Ocean "Arctic Ocean") and Atlantic oceans, east of the [Canadian Arctic Archipelago](/wiki/Arctic_Archipelago "Arctic Archipelago"). Greenland's [Kaffeklubben Island](/wiki/Kaffeklubben_Island "Kaffeklubben Island"), off the northern coast, is the world's [northernmost undisputed point of land](/wiki/Northernmost_point_of_land "Northernmost point of land")[[g]](#cite_note-24)‚Äî[Cape Morris Jesup](/wiki/Cape_Morris_Jesup "Cape Morris Jesup") on the mainland was thought to be so until the 1960s. The capital and largest city is [Nuuk](/wiki/Nuuk "Nuuk").[[16]](#cite_note-worldfactbook-21) Economically, Greenland is heavily reliant on [aid from Denmark](/wiki/Block_grant#Denmark "Block grant"), amounting to nearly half of the territory's total public revenue.
